{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|はね}}

Appears in the ''{{w|Wamyō Ruijushō}}'' of 938 CE.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Compound of {{compound|ja|sort=はね|羽|tr1=ha|t1=feather|根|tr2=ne|t2=root}}, originally referring specifically to where the [[quill]] of a [[feather]] attaches to the [[skin]].  Over time, the meaning broadened to refer to a [[feather]], and from there, to refer to a [[wing]].<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

{{ja-noun|はね}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=はね|archaic}} the [[portion]] of a [[feather]] where the [[quill]] [[attach]]es to the [[skin]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|羽茎|tr1=haguki|q1=rare|翮|tr2=kaku|q2=rare}}
# a [[feather]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|羽毛|tr1=umō}}
# a [[wing]] {{gloss|as of a [[bird]], [[bat]], [[insect]], or [[airplane]]}}
#: {{synonyms|ja|翼|tr1=tsubasa}}
# a [[fletching]] on an [[arrow]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|矢羽根|矢羽|tr2=yabane}}
# a [[shuttlecock]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|羽子|tr1=hago}}
# a [[blade]] (of a fan)

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|は}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=は|-}}.  Appears in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' of 712 CE, and the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.

May be cognate with {{m|ja|葉|tr=ha||leaf}}.

{{ja-noun|は}}

# a [[feather]] {{gloss|including [[synthetic]] feathers, as on a modern [[shuttlecock]]}}
